363 uint32 createProcExtendMask(SpellNonMeleeDamage* damageInfo, SpellMissInfo missCondition)
364 {
365  uint32 procEx = PROC_EX_NONE;
366  // Check victim state
367  if (missCondition != SPELL_MISS_NONE)
368  switch (missCondition)
369  {
370  case SPELL_MISS_MISS: procEx |= PROC_EX_MISS; break;
371  case SPELL_MISS_RESIST: procEx |= PROC_EX_RESIST; break;
372  case SPELL_MISS_DODGE: procEx |= PROC_EX_DODGE; break;
373  case SPELL_MISS_PARRY: procEx |= PROC_EX_PARRY; break;
374  case SPELL_MISS_BLOCK: procEx |= PROC_EX_BLOCK; break;
375  case SPELL_MISS_EVADE: procEx |= PROC_EX_EVADE; break;
376  case SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE: procEx |= PROC_EX_IMMUNE; break;
377  case SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE2: procEx |= PROC_EX_IMMUNE; break;
378  case SPELL_MISS_DEFLECT: procEx |= PROC_EX_DEFLECT; break;
379  case SPELL_MISS_ABSORB: procEx |= PROC_EX_ABSORB; break;
380  case SPELL_MISS_REFLECT: procEx |= PROC_EX_REFLECT; break;
381  default:
382  break;
383  }
384  else
385  {
386  // On block
387  if (damageInfo->blocked)
388  procEx |= PROC_EX_BLOCK;
389  // On absorb
390  if (damageInfo->absorb)
391  procEx |= PROC_EX_ABSORB;
392  // On crit
393  if (damageInfo->HitInfo & SPELL_HIT_TYPE_CRIT)
394  procEx |= PROC_EX_CRITICAL_HIT;
395  else
396  procEx |= PROC_EX_NORMAL_HIT;
397  }
398  return procEx;
399 }

401 void Unit::ProcSkillsAndReactives(bool isVictim, Unit* target, uint32 procFlags, uint32 procEx, WeaponAttackType attType)
402 {
403  // For melee/ranged based attack need update skills and set some Aura states
404  if (procFlags & MELEE_BASED_TRIGGER_MASK)
405  {
406  // Update skills here for players
407  if (GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
408  {
409  // On melee based hit/miss/resist need update skill (for victim and attacker)
410  if (procEx & (PROC_EX_NORMAL_HIT | PROC_EX_CRITICAL_HIT | PROC_EX_MISS | PROC_EX_DODGE | PROC_EX_PARRY | PROC_EX_BLOCK))
411  {
412  if (target->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER && target->GetCreatureType() != CREATURE_TYPE_CRITTER)
413  ((Player*)this)->UpdateCombatSkills(target, attType, isVictim);
414  }
415  // Update defence if player is victim and parry/dodge/block
416  if (isVictim && procEx & (PROC_EX_DODGE | PROC_EX_PARRY | PROC_EX_BLOCK))
417  ((Player*)this)->UpdateDefense();
418  }
419  // If exist crit/parry/dodge/block need update aura state (for victim and attacker)
420  if (procEx & (PROC_EX_CRITICAL_HIT | PROC_EX_PARRY | PROC_EX_DODGE | PROC_EX_BLOCK))
421  {
422  // for victim
423  if (isVictim)
424  {
425  // if victim and dodge attack
426  if (procEx & PROC_EX_DODGE)
427  {
428  // Update AURA_STATE on dodge
429  if (getClass() != CLASS_ROGUE) // skip Rogue Riposte
430  {
431  ModifyAuraState(AURA_STATE_DEFENSE, true);
432  StartReactiveTimer(REACTIVE_DEFENSE);
433  }
434  }
435  // if victim and parry attack
436  if (procEx & PROC_EX_PARRY)
437  {
438  // For Hunters only Counterattack (skip Mongoose bite)
439  if (getClass() == CLASS_HUNTER)
440  {
441  ModifyAuraState(AURA_STATE_HUNTER_PARRY, true);
442  StartReactiveTimer(REACTIVE_HUNTER_PARRY);
443  }
444  else
445  {
446  ModifyAuraState(AURA_STATE_DEFENSE, true);
447  StartReactiveTimer(REACTIVE_DEFENSE);
448  }
449  }
450  // if and victim block attack
451  if (procEx & PROC_EX_BLOCK)
452  {
453  ModifyAuraState(AURA_STATE_DEFENSE, true);
454  StartReactiveTimer(REACTIVE_DEFENSE);
455  }
456  }
457  else // For attacker
458  {
459  // Overpower on victim dodge
460  if (procEx & PROC_EX_DODGE && getClass() == CLASS_WARRIOR)
461  {
462  AddComboPoints(target, 1);
463  StartReactiveTimer(REACTIVE_OVERPOWER);
464  }
465  }
466  }
467  }
468 }

470 void Unit::ProcDamageAndSpell(ProcSystemArguments&& data)
471 {
472  // First lets get skills and reactives out of the way
473  bool currentLevel = true;
474  if (data.attacker)
475  {
476  if (data.attacker->m_spellProcsHappening)
477  currentLevel = false; // triggered spell in proc system should not make holders ready
478  data.attacker->m_spellProcsHappening = true;
479  if (data.procFlagsAttacker)
480  data.attacker->ProcSkillsAndReactives(false, data.victim, data.procFlagsAttacker, data.procExtra, data.attType);
481  }
482  bool canProcVictim = data.victim && data.victim->IsAlive() && data.procFlagsVictim;
483  if (canProcVictim)
484  data.victim->ProcSkillsAndReactives(true, data.attacker, data.procFlagsVictim, data.procExtra, data.attType);
485 
486  // Not much to do if no flags are set.
487  if (data.attacker && data.procFlagsAttacker)
488  data.attacker->ProcDamageAndSpellFor(data, false);
489 
490  // Now go on with a victim's events'n'auras
491  // Not much to do if no flags are set or there is no victim
492  if (canProcVictim)
493  data.victim->ProcDamageAndSpellFor(data, true);
494 
495  if (data.attacker)
496  {
497  // trigger weapon enchants for weapon based spells; exclude spells that stop attack, because may break CC
498  if (data.attacker->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && (data.procExtra & (PROC_EX_NORMAL_HIT | PROC_EX_CRITICAL_HIT)) != 0)
499  if ((data.procFlagsAttacker & PROC_FLAG_DEAL_HARMFUL_PERIODIC) == 0) // do not proc this on DOTs
500  if (!data.spellInfo || (data.spellInfo->EquippedItemClass == ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON && !data.spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX4_SUPPRESS_WEAPON_PROCS)))
501  static_cast<Player*>(data.attacker)->CastItemCombatSpell(data.victim, data.attType, data.spellInfo ? !IsNextMeleeSwingSpell(data.spellInfo) : false);
502 
503  if (currentLevel)
504  {
505  data.attacker->m_spellProcsHappening = false;
506 
507  // Mark auras created during proccing as ready
508  for (SpellAuraHolder* holder : data.attacker->m_delayedSpellAuraHolders)
509  if (holder->GetState() == SPELLAURAHOLDER_STATE_CREATED) // if deleted by some unknown circumstance
510  holder->SetState(SPELLAURAHOLDER_STATE_READY);
511 
512  data.attacker->m_delayedSpellAuraHolders.clear();
513  }
514  }
515 }

518  isVictim(isVictim), procExtra(data.procExtra), attType(data.attType), damage(data.damage), spellInfo(data.spellInfo), spell(data.spell), healthGain(data.healthGain), isHeal(data.isHeal),
519  triggeredByAura(nullptr), cooldown(0), triggeredSpellId(0), procOnce(false), triggerTarget(nullptr)

522  {
523  source = data.victim;
524  target = data.attacker;
525  procFlags = data.procFlagsVictim;
526  }
527  else
528  {
529  source = data.attacker;
530  target = data.victim;
531  procFlags = data.procFlagsAttacker;
532  }

535 void Unit::ProcDamageAndSpellFor(ProcSystemArguments& argData, bool isVictim)
536 {
537  ProcExecutionData execData(argData, isVictim);
538 
539  ProcTriggeredList procTriggered;
540  std::vector<SpellAuraHolder*> holdersForDeletion;
541  // Fill procTriggered list
542  for (SpellAuraHolderMap::const_iterator itr = GetSpellAuraHolderMap().begin(); itr != GetSpellAuraHolderMap().end(); ++itr)
543  {
544  SpellAuraHolder* holder = itr->second;
545  // skip deleted auras (possible at recursive triggered call
546  if (holder->GetState() != SPELLAURAHOLDER_STATE_READY || holder->IsDeleted())
547  continue;
548 
549  SpellProcEventEntry const* spellProcEvent = nullptr;
550  SpellProcEventTriggerCheck result = IsTriggeredAtSpellProcEvent(execData, holder, spellProcEvent);
551  if (holder->GetSpellProto()->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_PROC_FAILURE_BURNS_CHARGE) &&
552  result == SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_ROLL_FAILED && holder->GetAuraCharges() > 0)
553  holdersForDeletion.push_back(holder);
554 
555  if (holder->GetSpellProto()->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX2_PROC_COOLDOWN_ON_FAILURE) && result == SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_ROLL_FAILED)
556  {
557  uint32 cooldown = 0;
558  if (spellProcEvent && spellProcEvent->cooldown)
559  cooldown = spellProcEvent->cooldown;
560  if (cooldown)
561  holder->SetProcCooldown(std::chrono::seconds(cooldown), GetMap()->GetCurrentClockTime());
562  }
563 
564  if (result != SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_OK)
565  continue;
566 
567  procTriggered.push_back(ProcTriggeredData(spellProcEvent, itr->second));
568  }
569 
570  for (SpellAuraHolder* holder : holdersForDeletion)
571  if (holder->DropAuraCharge())
572  RemoveSpellAuraHolder(holder);
573 
574  // Nothing found
575  if (procTriggered.empty())
576  return;
577 
578  // Handle effects proceed this time
579  for (ProcTriggeredList::const_iterator itr = procTriggered.begin(); itr != procTriggered.end(); ++itr)
580  {
581  // Some auras can be deleted in function called in this loop (except first, ofc)
582  SpellAuraHolder* triggeredByHolder = itr->triggeredByHolder;
583  if (triggeredByHolder->IsDeleted())
584  continue;
585 
586  SpellProcEventEntry const* spellProcEvent = itr->spellProcEvent;
587  bool useCharges = triggeredByHolder->GetAuraCharges() > 0;
588  bool procSuccess = true;
589  bool anyAuraProc = false;
590 
591  execData.cooldown = 0;
592  if (spellProcEvent && spellProcEvent->cooldown)
593  execData.cooldown = spellProcEvent->cooldown;
594 
595  for (int32 i = 0; i < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++i)
596  {
597  execData.triggeredByAura = triggeredByHolder->GetAuraByEffectIndex(SpellEffectIndex(i));
598  if (!execData.triggeredByAura)
599  continue;
600 
601  Modifier* auraModifier = execData.triggeredByAura->GetModifier();
602 
603  if (execData.spellInfo)
604  {
605  if (spellProcEvent)
606  {
607  if (spellProcEvent->spellFamilyMask[i])
608  {
609  if (!execData.spellInfo->IsFitToFamilyMask(spellProcEvent->spellFamilyMask[i]))
610  continue;
611 
612  // don't allow proc from cast end for non modifier spells
613  // unless they have proc ex defined for that
614  if (IsCastEndProcModifierAura(triggeredByHolder->GetSpellProto(), SpellEffectIndex(i), execData.spellInfo))
615  {
616  if (useCharges && execData.procExtra != PROC_EX_CAST_END && spellProcEvent->procEx == PROC_EX_NONE)
617  continue;
618  }
619  else if (spellProcEvent->procEx == PROC_EX_NONE && execData.procExtra == PROC_EX_CAST_END)
620  continue;
621  }
622  // don't check dbc FamilyFlags if schoolMask exists
623  else if (!execData.triggeredByAura->CanProcFrom(execData.spellInfo, execData.procFlags, spellProcEvent->procEx, execData.procExtra, execData.damage != 0, !spellProcEvent->schoolMask))
624  continue;
625  }
626  else if (!execData.triggeredByAura->CanProcFrom(execData.spellInfo, execData.procFlags, PROC_EX_NONE, execData.procExtra, execData.damage != 0, true))
627  continue;
628  }
629 
630  execData.triggeredSpellId = 0;
631  execData.basepoints = { 0, 0, 0 };
632  SpellAuraProcResult procResult = execData.triggeredByAura->OnProc(execData);
633  if (procResult == SPELL_AURA_PROC_OK)
634  procResult = (*this.*AuraProcHandler[auraModifier->m_auraname])(execData);
635  switch (procResult)
636  {
637  case SPELL_AURA_PROC_CANT_TRIGGER:
638  continue;
639  case SPELL_AURA_PROC_FAILED:
640  // example - drain soul vanilla - third effect fails when not have talent but charge should drop
641  if (!triggeredByHolder->GetSpellProto()->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_PROC_FAILURE_BURNS_CHARGE))
642  procSuccess = false;
643  break;
644  case SPELL_AURA_PROC_OK:
645  if (execData.procOnce && execData.spell)
646  execData.spell->RegisterAuraProc(execData.triggeredByAura);
647  break;
648  }
649 
650  anyAuraProc = true;
651  }
652 
653  if (procSuccess && execData.cooldown)
654  triggeredByHolder->SetProcCooldown(std::chrono::seconds(execData.cooldown), GetMap()->GetCurrentClockTime());
655 
656  // Remove charge (aura can be removed by triggers)
657  if (useCharges && procSuccess && anyAuraProc && !triggeredByHolder->IsDeleted())
658  {
659  // If last charge dropped add spell to remove list
660  if (triggeredByHolder->DropAuraCharge())
661  RemoveSpellAuraHolder(triggeredByHolder);
662  }
663  }
664 }
665 
666 Unit::SpellProcEventTriggerCheck Unit::IsTriggeredAtSpellProcEvent(ProcExecutionData& data, SpellAuraHolder* holder, SpellProcEventEntry const*& spellProcEvent)
667 {
668  SpellEntry const* spellProto = holder->GetSpellProto();
669 
670  // Get proc Event Entry
671  spellProcEvent = sSpellMgr.GetSpellProcEvent(spellProto->Id);
672 
673  // Get EventProcFlag
674  uint32 EventProcFlag;
675  if (spellProcEvent && spellProcEvent->procFlags) // if exist get custom spellProcEvent->procFlags
676  EventProcFlag = spellProcEvent->procFlags;
677  else
678  EventProcFlag = spellProto->procFlags; // else get from spell proto
679  // Continue if no trigger exist
680  if (!EventProcFlag)
681  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_FAILED;
682 
683  // Check spellProcEvent data requirements
684  if (!SpellMgr::IsSpellProcEventCanTriggeredBy(spellProcEvent, EventProcFlag, data.spellInfo, data.procFlags, data.procExtra))
685  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_FAILED;
686 
687  // In most cases req get honor or XP from kill
688  if (EventProcFlag & PROC_FLAG_KILL && GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
689  {
690  bool allow = ((Player*)this)->isHonorOrXPTarget(data.target);
691  // Shadow Word: Death - can trigger from every kill
692  if (holder->GetId() == 32409)
693  allow = true;
694  if (!allow)
695  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_FAILED;
696  }
697  // Aura added by spell can`t trigger from self (prevent drop charges/do triggers)
698  // But except periodic triggers (can triggered from self)
699  if (data.spellInfo && data.spellInfo->Id == spellProto->Id && !(EventProcFlag & PROC_FLAG_TAKE_HARMFUL_PERIODIC))
700  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_FAILED;
701 
702  // Check if current equipment allows aura to proc
703  if (!data.isVictim && GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && !spellProto->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX3_NO_PROC_EQUIP_REQUIREMENT))
704  {
705  if (spellProto->EquippedItemClass == ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON)
706  {
707  Item* item = nullptr;
708  switch (data.attType)
709  {
710  default:
711  case BASE_ATTACK:
712  item = ((Player*)this)->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND);
713  break;
714  case OFF_ATTACK:
715  item = ((Player*)this)->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND);
716  break;
717  case RANGED_ATTACK:
718  item = ((Player*)this)->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_RANGED);
719  break;
720  }
721 
722  if (!CanUseEquippedWeapon(data.attType))
723  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_FAILED;
724 
725  if (!item || item->IsBroken() || item->GetProto()->Class != ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON || !((1 << item->GetProto()->SubClass) & spellProto->EquippedItemSubClassMask))
726  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_FAILED;
727  }
728  else if (spellProto->EquippedItemClass == ITEM_CLASS_ARMOR)
729  {
730  // Check if player is wearing shield
731  Item* item = ((Player*)this)->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND);
732  if (!item || item->IsBroken() || item->GetProto()->Class != ITEM_CLASS_ARMOR || !((1 << item->GetProto()->SubClass) & spellProto->EquippedItemSubClassMask))
733  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_FAILED;
734  }
735  }
736 
737  if (spellProto->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX3_ONLY_PROC_OUTDOORS) && !GetTerrain()->IsOutdoors(GetPositionX(), GetPositionY(), GetPositionZ()))
738  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_FAILED;
739 
740  if (spellProto->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX3_ONLY_PROC_ON_CASTER) && holder->GetTarget()->GetObjectGuid() != holder->GetCasterGuid())
741  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_FAILED;
742 
743  if (IsSitState() && !spellProto->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_ALLOW_WHILE_SITTING) && !spellProto->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX4_ALLOW_PROC_WHILE_SITTING))
744  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_FAILED;
745 
746  if (data.isVictim && data.spellInfo && data.spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX3_SUPPRESS_TARGET_PROCS) && !spellProto->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX7_CAN_PROC_FROM_SUPPRESSED_TARGET_PROCS))
747  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_FAILED;
748 
749  // Get chance from spell
750  float chance = (float)spellProto->procChance;
751  // If in spellProcEvent exist custom chance, chance = spellProcEvent->customChance;
752  if (spellProcEvent && spellProcEvent->customChance)
753  chance = spellProcEvent->customChance;
754  // If PPM exist calculate chance from PPM
755  if (!data.isVictim && spellProcEvent && spellProcEvent->ppmRate != 0)
756  {
757  uint32 WeaponSpeed = GetAttackTime(data.attType);
758  chance = GetPPMProcChance(WeaponSpeed, spellProcEvent->ppmRate);
759  }
760  // Apply chance modifier aura
761  if (Player* modOwner = GetSpellModOwner())
762  {
763  modOwner->ApplySpellMod(spellProto->Id, SPELLMOD_CHANCE_OF_SUCCESS, chance);
764  modOwner->ApplySpellMod(spellProto->Id, SPELLMOD_FREQUENCY_OF_SUCCESS, chance);
765  }
766 
767  // proc chance is reduced by an additional 3.333% per level past 60
768  if (holder->IsReducedProcChancePast60() && GetLevel() > 60)
769  chance = std::max(0.f, (1.f - ((GetLevel() - 60) * 1.f / 30.f)) * chance);
770 
771  if (data.spell)
772  {
773  if (spellProto->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX6_AURA_IS_WEAPON_PROC) && data.spell->m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX4_SUPPRESS_WEAPON_PROCS))
774  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_FAILED;
775 
776  if (data.spell->m_IsTriggeredSpell)
777  {
778  if (!data.spell->m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX3_NOT_A_PROC) && !spellProto->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX3_CAN_PROC_FROM_PROCS))
779  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_FAILED;
780  }
781 
782  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++i)
783  if (Aura* aura = holder->m_auras[i])
784  if (data.spell->IsAuraProcced(aura))
785  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_FAILED;
786  }
787 
788  for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_EFFECT_INDEX; ++i)
789  if (Aura* aura = holder->m_auras[i])
790  if (!aura->OnCheckProc(data))
791  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_FAILED;
792 
793  if (roll_chance_f(chance))
794  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_OK;
795  else
796  return SpellProcEventTriggerCheck::SPELL_PROC_TRIGGER_ROLL_FAILED;
797 }

799 SpellAuraProcResult Unit::TriggerProccedSpell(Unit* target, std::array<int32, MAX_EFFECT_INDEX>& basepoints, uint32 triggeredSpellId, Item* castItem, Aura* triggeredByAura, uint32 cooldown, ObjectGuid originalCaster)

812 SpellAuraProcResult Unit::TriggerProccedSpell(Unit* target, std::array<int32, MAX_EFFECT_INDEX>& basepoints, SpellEntry const* spellInfo, Item* castItem, Aura* triggeredByAura, uint32 cooldown, ObjectGuid originalCaster)
813 {
814  // default case
815  if (!target && IsSpellRequireTarget(spellInfo))
816  return SPELL_AURA_PROC_FAILED;
817 
818  if (target && (target != this && !target->IsAlive()))
819  return SPELL_AURA_PROC_FAILED;
820 
821  if (!triggeredByAura->GetHolder()->IsProcReady(GetMap()->GetCurrentClockTime()))
822  return SPELL_AURA_PROC_FAILED;
823 
824  if (basepoints[EFFECT_INDEX_0] || basepoints[EFFECT_INDEX_1] || basepoints[EFFECT_INDEX_2])
825  CastCustomSpell(target, spellInfo,
826  basepoints[EFFECT_INDEX_0] ? &basepoints[EFFECT_INDEX_0] : nullptr,
827  basepoints[EFFECT_INDEX_1] ? &basepoints[EFFECT_INDEX_1] : nullptr,
828  basepoints[EFFECT_INDEX_2] ? &basepoints[EFFECT_INDEX_2] : nullptr,
829  TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED | TRIGGERED_INSTANT_CAST | TRIGGERED_DO_NOT_RESET_LEASH, castItem, triggeredByAura, originalCaster);
830  else
831  CastSpell(target, spellInfo, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED | TRIGGERED_INSTANT_CAST | TRIGGERED_DO_NOT_RESET_LEASH, castItem, triggeredByAura, originalCaster);
832 
833  if (cooldown)
834  triggeredByAura->GetHolder()->SetProcCooldown(std::chrono::seconds(cooldown), GetMap()->GetCurrentClockTime());
835 
836  return SPELL_AURA_PROC_OK;
837 }

3939 SpellAuraProcResult Unit::HandleProcTriggerDamageAuraProc(ProcExecutionData& data)
3940 {
3941  Unit* victim = data.target; Aura* triggeredByAura = data.triggeredByAura; uint32 cooldown = data.cooldown;
3942  SpellEntry const* spellInfo = triggeredByAura->GetSpellProto();
3943  DEBUG_FILTER_LOG(LOG_FILTER_SPELL_CAST, "ProcDamageAndSpell: doing %u damage from spell id %u (triggered by auratype %u of spell %u)",
3944  triggeredByAura->GetModifier()->m_amount, spellInfo->Id, triggeredByAura->GetModifier()->m_auraname, triggeredByAura->GetId());
3945 
3946  if (!triggeredByAura->GetHolder()->IsProcReady(GetMap()->GetCurrentClockTime()))
3947  return SPELL_AURA_PROC_FAILED;
3948 
3949  // Trigger damage can be resisted...
3950  if (SpellMissInfo missInfo = SpellHitResult(this, victim, spellInfo, uint8(1 << triggeredByAura->GetEffIndex()), false))
3951  {
3952  SendSpellDamageResist(victim, spellInfo->Id);
3953  return SPELL_AURA_PROC_OK;
3954  }
3955 
3956  if (cooldown)
3957  triggeredByAura->GetHolder()->SetProcCooldown(std::chrono::seconds(cooldown), GetMap()->GetCurrentClockTime());
3958 
3959  SpellNonMeleeDamage spellDamageInfo(this, victim, spellInfo->Id, SpellSchoolMask(spellInfo->SchoolMask));
3960  CalculateSpellDamage(&spellDamageInfo, triggeredByAura->GetModifier()->m_amount, spellInfo);
3961  spellDamageInfo.target->CalculateAbsorbResistBlock(this, &spellDamageInfo, spellInfo);
3962  Unit::DealDamageMods(this, spellDamageInfo.target, spellDamageInfo.damage, &spellDamageInfo.absorb, SPELL_DIRECT_DAMAGE);
3963  SendSpellNonMeleeDamageLog(&spellDamageInfo);
3964  DealSpellDamage(this, &spellDamageInfo, true, false);
3965  return SPELL_AURA_PROC_OK;
3966 }
